hkGQjAMJ8zwxGa1iZLQbW7EN6FhOdIEZq_JlNKp0qM7Sg7VE7FWDscJ40Vu6lcf7-O1Olr\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class naming and structure**\\n\\nI'm wondering if the helper class name should relate directly to the dynamic-access class, maintaining a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files. It seems like there could be just one test file for ManifestInfo, and maybe the helper file can be a top level in the same file. I'll need to keep in mind the warning about not using \\\"$\\\" in test class or file names. Could I make the helper private instead?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Refined `ManifestInfoTest.scala` to make the remaining call site execute deterministically.\n\nUpdated:\n\n- `tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-actor_2.13/2.8.8/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_actor_2_13/ManifestInfoTest.scala`\n\nChanges made:\n\n- Creates a temporary valid `META-INF/MANIFEST.MF` resource.\n- Supplies it through a dedicated `ClassLoader` to the `ActorSystem`.\n- Directly constructs `akka.util.ManifestInfo` with the system’s `ExtendedActorSystem`, ensuring `system.dynamicAccess.classLoader.getResources(\"META-INF/MANIFEST.MF\")` is reached inside `ManifestInfo`.\n- Verifies the discovered `akka-actor` version using `akka.Version.current`, avoiding hardcoded artifact versions.\n\nPer instructions, I did not run tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c2f72ae2b6870480169fb2cb3e15481968907d3bcee6cfef9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1270, "output": 758, "cacheRead": 36864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38892, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778068646930, "responseId": "resp_0c2f72ae2b6870480169fb2ca899cc8196a777526734f3ee91"}}
